Five members of Awawa boys have been arrested by the Rapid Response Squad (RRS) of the Lagos State Police Command. They were apprehended on Thursday in their hideouts in Mulero, Orile Agege, Abule Egba and Agege. The police said the three suspects were nabbed on Wednesday and handed over to the divisional police units in respective areas. The gang and others had unleashed terror on Mulero and parts of Iyana Ipaja, Tuesday night. RRS Commander, Olayinka Egbeyemi, on the order of CP Abiodun Alabi, deployed officers to the affected areas. “Recovered from one of the suspects were wraps of substances believed to be Indian hemp and ice,” the police disclosed. The statement added that those in custody in connection with the disturbance will be charged to court.